---
import GuideLayout from '../layouts/GuideLayout.astro';
import { SITE_NAME, SITE_URL } from '../lib/seo';
---

<GuideLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - UK Salary and Tax Calculator Website"
  description="Our privacy policy explains how we handle your data. No cookies, no tracking and no salary data stored. All tax calculations run entirely in your browser."
  slug="/privacy/"
>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><em>Last updated: June 2026</em></p>

  <p>
    This privacy policy explains how {SITE_NAME} ({SITE_URL}) handles your personal data in compliance
    with the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR), the Data Protection Act 2018, and the
    Privacy and Electronic Communications Regulations 2003 (PECR).
  </p>

  <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Controller:</strong> Mottalib Radif</li>
    <li><strong>Website:</strong> {SITE_URL}</li>
    <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:contact@realsalary.co.uk">contact@realsalary.co.uk</a></li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    The data controller is the person who determines the purposes and means of the processing of
    personal data, within the meaning of the UK GDPR.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Data Protection Officer</h2>
  <p>
    Given the nature of the website and the absence of large-scale processing of personal data, the
    appointment of a Data Protection Officer (DPO) is not legally required under Article 37 of the
    UK GDPR. For data protection enquiries, please contact the controller using the details above.
  </p>

  <h2>3. What Data We Collect</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Short answer: almost nothing.</strong> All calculator inputs are processed entirely in your
    browser using client-side JavaScript. We never see, store, or transmit your salary figures, tax
    codes, pension contributions, or any other financial information you enter into our calculators.
    The technical architecture is designed according to the principle of "privacy by design".
  </p>
  <p>
    For clarity, the website does not collect or process the following categories of data:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Financial data:</strong> salary, tax code, pension contributions, National Insurance number</li>
    <li><strong>Identification data:</strong> name, address, phone number (unless voluntarily provided by email)</li>
    <li><strong>Browsing data:</strong> tracking cookies, unique device identifiers</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    We use <a href="https://plausible.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Plausible Analytics</a>,
    a privacy-friendly analytics tool. Plausible does not use cookies, does not collect personal data,
    does not store IP addresses, does not use fingerprinting, and is fully compliant with UK GDPR,
    GDPR, CCPA, and PECR. This means <strong>no cookie banner is needed</strong>.
  </p>
  <p>
    Plausible collects only aggregate, anonymous data: page views, referral sources, browser type,
    device type, and country. No individual visitors can be identified. Plausible processes all data
    on servers within the European Union. For more information:
    <a href="https://plausible.io/data-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://plausible.io/data-policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    We do not set any tracking cookies. No first-party cookies, no third-party cookies, no tracking
    cookies. User preferences (such as dark/light mode) are stored in the browser's localStorage,
    which is not a cookie and is never transmitted to our servers.
  </p>
  <p>
    Our hosting provider Cloudflare may use a technical cookie (__cf_bm) for bot detection and DDoS
    protection. This cookie is strictly necessary for security, contains no personal information,
    expires after 30 minutes, and does not require consent under PECR.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>
    This site is hosted on Cloudflare Pages. Cloudflare may collect minimal technical data (IP address,
    request headers) as part of their CDN service. Cloudflare is certified under the EU-U.S. Data
    Privacy Framework. See
    <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare's privacy policy</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    Google Fonts may be loaded for typography. Google may collect standard web request data. See
    <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google's privacy policy</a>.
    This usage is based on our legitimate interest in a uniform presentation of our website.
  </p>
  <p>
    We do not integrate any third-party services that profile users. There are no social media buttons,
    advertising widgets, remarketing services, or other tools that allow third parties to track users.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Server Log Files</h2>
  <p>
    Our hosting provider automatically collects and stores information in server log files, which your
    browser transmits. These include: browser type and version, operating system, referrer URL, hostname,
    time of request, and IP address (anonymised). This data is not merged with other data sources and
    is based on legitimate interest (Art. 6(1)(f) UK GDPR). Server log files are automatically deleted
    after 30 days.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
  <p>
    Since no identifiable personal data is processed through the calculators, no specific legal basis
    is required under Article 6 of the UK GDPR. For the anonymous statistical data collected by
    Plausible Analytics and for server log files, the applicable legal basis is legitimate interest
    (Article 6(1)(f) UK GDPR).
  </p>

  <h2>9. Your Rights Under UK GDPR</h2>
  <p>
    Under the UK GDPR and Data Protection Act 2018, you have the following rights:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Right of access</strong> (Art. 15): obtain confirmation of whether personal data is being processed and access to that data.</li>
    <li><strong>Right to rectification</strong> (Art. 16): obtain correction of inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
    <li><strong>Right to erasure</strong> (Art. 17, "right to be forgotten"): obtain deletion of personal data.</li>
    <li><strong>Right to restriction of processing</strong> (Art. 18): restrict processing in certain cases.</li>
    <li><strong>Right to data portability</strong> (Art. 20): receive data in a structured, commonly used and machine-readable format.</li>
    <li><strong>Right to object</strong> (Art. 21): object to processing on grounds relating to your particular situation.</li>
    <li><strong>Right to withdraw consent</strong> (Art. 7(3)): withdraw consent at any time.</li>
    <li><strong>Right to lodge a complaint</strong>: with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a>.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Since we don't collect personal data through our calculators, most of these rights are satisfied
    by default. For any privacy-related questions, contact us at
    <a href="mailto:contact@realsalary.co.uk">contact@realsalary.co.uk</a>. We undertake to respond
    within 30 days.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Data Transfer Outside the UK</h2>
  <p>
    Cloudflare, our hosting provider, is certified under the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework, ensuring
    compliance with data protection standards. Should it become necessary to use services outside
    adequate jurisdictions, the controller will ensure appropriate safeguards are in place.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Data Retention</h2>
  <p>
    Since no personal data is stored from calculator usage, no specific retention period applies. Server
    log files are automatically deleted after 30 days. Plausible Analytics data is aggregated and
    anonymous, falling outside the scope of UK GDPR provisions on personal data retention.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Our website is not directed to children under 13 and we do not knowingly collect personal
    information from children.
  </p>

  <h2>13. Changes and Contact</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this privacy policy to reflect changes in our practices or applicable law. The
    current version is always available on this page. For questions, contact us at:<br />
    <a href="mailto:contact@realsalary.co.uk">contact@realsalary.co.uk</a>
  </p>
</GuideLayout>
